CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 1, 1969, pg. 16, reads: "Banquet Committee - Members of the Founder's Day Banquet committee of the alumni chapter of Kappa Alpha Psi are pictured here with principal speaker, Dr. William "Stud" Greene of Washington, D.C. banquet took place at Stouffers Restaurant in Oakland. Seated from left: Ralph Barnett, chairman; Dr. Greene and George Charlton, Polemarch.  Standing from left: William W. Goode, James Greenlee, Robert W. Smith Jr., Arthur Burt and Henry Tate."Seated first row, from left: Bob Smith, Arthur Burt, Rev. James B. Brown, Rev. James B. Cayce, Dr. Henry "Stud" Green, George Charlton, Ralph Barnett, Lorenzo Hill, Bailey O. Holland, unknown, and Robert Williams; second row: three unknown men, John Smith, three unknown men, James Greenlee, three unknown men, Stanford Evans, Russell Washington, two unknown men, James Laughton, Dr. Leon Ford, unknown, Jonas Hood, Marshall Johnson, Alfred Carl, and two unknown men; third row: two unknown men, Andrew Turner, two unknown men, Howard Hailstork, unknown man, Moses Davis, three unknown men, Fred Gladney, and unknown man.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity members, gathered behind banquet table in Stouffers Restaurant for Founder's Day banquet, another version
